"That is the default option but not the only one.  It forces the contractor "
"to assign ownership of the copyrights in the code and the documentation that "
"it generates."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/legal-aspects.adoc:45
msgid ""
"It particularly makes sense that the City Council should wish to concentrate "
"all property rights on emblematic projects, principally used between public "
"administrations, and on those over which it intends to decide to a large "
"extent the rules of governance."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/legal-aspects.adoc:49
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Assign ownership of the new source code to the legal owner of the original "
"code"
msgstr ""

#.  links incoming: link:#M_4DC[_M_4DC_]
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/legal-aspects.adoc:59
msgid ""
"When we adapt an existing product, to accept the inclusion of our code in "
"the original product we may be asked to sign a Contributor Licence Agreement "
"(CLA) or equivalent contract.  If not, the parts developed by the City "
"Council can be owned by it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/legal-aspects.adoc:63
#, no-wrap
msgid "Assign ownership of the source code to an independent non-profit"
msgstr ""

#.  links incoming: link:#M_4DC[_M_4DC_]
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/legal-aspects.adoc:77
msgid ""
"There is a third option if the aim is for ownership to eventually go to an "
"external organisation responsible for the running and governance of the "
"project in the long term.  Given the nature of the function, that "
"organisation will normally take the legal form of a foundation or other "
"non-profit entity.  This makes sense in projects where, besides the City "
"Council, other public, private or third sector bodies are involved "
"financially and in decision-making.  In this case copyright must be assigned "
"by contract, either directly to the corresponding entity, or initially to "
"the City Council, so the latter can assign copyright to the entity at a "
"later date."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/legal-aspects.adoc:79
msgid ""
"The foundation can manage other projects freed by the City Council or of "
"other entities linked with the public sphere."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
